C5 done. Now C6 — the classifier that decides which of the three states we're in.
A Switch action needs something deterministic to switch on. We can't switch directly on "the array length" + "the value of _pei_targetbu_value" in one go — Switch takes a single expression. So we build a Compose action just above the Switch that classifies the state into a single string ("NotFound" / "Resolved" / "Unmapped"), then Switch branches on that string.
This is the same Compose-classify-then-Switch pattern L1-A07 Phase C Option-D used (per the May 3 backup notes in the registry). Mirroring it keeps the two BU resolution chains structurally identical and auditable.

