Step 6a-2 — Inputs field — click into it, switch to fx mode, paste:
if(equals(length(outputs('Find_BP_Mapping')?['body/value']), 0), 'NotFound', if(equals(coalesce(first(outputs('Find_BP_Mapping')?['body/value'])?['_pei_targetbu_value'], ''), ''), 'Unmapped', 'Resolved'))
What this expression does
Reading inside-out:

length(outputs('Find_BP_Mapping')?['body/value']) — array length of mapping rows returned (0 or 1, since Row count = 1)
Outer if(equals(..., 0), 'NotFound', ...) — if array empty, classify as NotFound
Otherwise drop into nested check: first(...)?['_pei_targetbu_value'] reads the Target BU raw GUID from the single row
coalesce(..., '') treats null/missing as empty string
Inner if(equals(..., ''), 'Unmapped', 'Resolved') — empty Target BU = Unmapped, anything else = Resolved

So the Compose output is exactly one of three strings: 'NotFound', 'Unmapped', or 'Resolved'.
